Step beads are labeled "step" and have notes with sequence:N values. Any child without the "step" label is review feedback from a prior iteration.

Evaluate: Are steps well-scoped? Well-ordered (check notes sequence values)? Missing steps? Steps that should be split or merged?

If steps need reordering, renumbering, insertion, or removal, file a child issue describing the change (do NOT label it "step" — only the implement agent creates step beads). The next implement iteration will update the step beads accordingly.

File child issues for any adjustments needed. After your review, write a brief summary (2-4 sentences) of your overall assessment as your FINAL output. If you filed issues, summarize what you found. If the decomposition is ready with no issues filed, respond with exactly: "No further improvements needed."

IMPORTANT: Your summary text MUST be the very last thing you output. Do not end on a tool call. The summary is captured and displayed to the human operator.

Rules:
- Every issue you file MUST include a tier tag in the title: [T1], [T2], [T3], or [T4].
  [T1] Correctness — step ordering would cause build/test failures or data loss.
  [T2] Completeness — a required step is missing or a step is too coarse to be one commit.
  [T3] Design — steps work but could be better scoped or ordered.
  [T4] Polish — minor naming or organizational preferences.
  Example title: "[T2] Missing step for database migration between steps 3 and 4"
- If a section is marked as frozen in the Convergence Context below, do not file issues about it unless you've identified a Tier 1 (correctness) bug.
